Program: Outlook
Title: 05/12/2011
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00lw94g
Last Broadcast Date: Tue 6 Dec 2011
Extraordinary personal stories from around the world. Today, astronaut Diego Urbina describes what it was like being locked inside a space capsule in Russia for almost 18 months as part of a simulated trip to Mars. Also, the Indonesian Muslim who was sent a letter bomb because of his campaign against extremism. And British woman, Rona Cant, who suddenly took up adventuring in middle age - she started by sailing the wrong way around the world. Rona's book is called Snow, Sleds and Silence: The Story of the Nordkapp Expedition and is published by Libri. (Image: Diego Urbina. Credit: AFP/Getty) Show less